<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4547152>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. — Annulobalcis wareni n. sp.: A, B, holotype (MNHN 24192); C, D, paratype 1 (ZIN 61121); E, paratype 2 (MNHN 24193); F, specimen 1 (Table 5) collected from the same host as the sequenced ones; G-J, specimen 2 (Table 5) collected from the same host as the sequenced ones; G, operculum, SEM; H, SEM of the shell; I, J, apex in different views, SEM. Scale bars: A-F, H, 1 mm; G, 500 μm; I, 200 μm; J, 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4547152/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4547160>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. — A, live specimen of Annulobalcis albus n. sp.; B, Annulobalcis albus n. sp. specimens on their host Oxycomanthus benetti (Müller, 1841); C, Annulobalcis vinarius n. sp. on arm of crinoid Himerometra robustipinna Carpenter, 1881; D, live specimen of Annulobalcis vinarius n. sp.; E, eggs capsules of Annulobalcis vinarius n. sp. on crinoid Himerometra robustipinna; F, live specimen of Annulobalcis wareni n. sp. Scale bars: A, C-F, 1 mm; B, 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4547160/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

